1
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,980
Episode 26

2
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,120
Here, look this way.

3
00:01:40,430 --> 00:01:41,430
A little bit closer.

4
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,430
Look at me.

5
00:01:44,510 --> 00:01:46,280
Three, two, one.

6
00:01:47,790 --> 00:01:48,230
Alright.

7
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:49,950
The news will be

8
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:50,920
available this afternoon.

9
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:51,870
So soon?

10
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:52,760
Yeah.

11
00:01:52,790 --> 00:01:54,150
It's the age of the internet now.

12
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,350
You see,

13
00:01:55,790 --> 00:01:57,040
I interviewed Mr. Gao last night

14
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:57,950
and edited it afterward.

15
00:01:58,070 --> 00:01:59,040
This morning,

16
00:01:59,070 --> 00:01:59,920
I uploaded it,

17
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:01,920
and it already got a lot of views.

18
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,480
Wait...

19
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,920
Founder Gao Xiang sold his shares.

20
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,350
Skymind changed hands.

21
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:09,590
Gao Xiang sold his company?

22
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:10,520
Yeah.

23
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,150
You didn't know about that?

24
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:15,120
Mr. Gao really is a master of the game.

25
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,470
He's great at business.

26
00:02:16,590 --> 00:02:17,150
He doesn't

27
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:18,080
even want to be

28
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:18,870
a co-CEO.

29
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:21,080
He just cashed out

30
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,800
and walked away.

31
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,360
What a slick move.

32
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,560
I heard that

33
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,520
he made a fortune recently.

34
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:32,360
Here!

35
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:35,150
Excuse me?

36
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:36,280
More drinks!

37
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:36,910
Coming right up!

38
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:41,470
I suggest

39
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:43,680
we all toast

40
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:44,590
to Mr. Gao,

41
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:45,280
okay?

42
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,310
Okay!

43
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:48,800
Mr. Gao! Let's toast to Mr. Gao!

44
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,430
Thank you, Mr. Gao! Cheers!

45
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:56,430
Drink up!

46
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:56,870
Everyone!

47
00:02:56,870 --> 00:02:57,630
Drink up! Come on!

48
00:02:59,360 --> 00:02:59,910
Nice wine.

49
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,360
Hey, Fang Wanzhi.

50
00:03:04,310 --> 00:03:05,120
I know you're busy,

51
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:06,520
so I haven't called you.

52
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:08,840
What?

53
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,310
Let's have dinner, then.

54
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,150
I'll send the address.

55
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:15,680
I'm glad you can come.

56
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:17,400
Someone will surely be happy.

57
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:24,840
Don't just toast to me.

58
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,560
Let's all toast to Mr. Li!

59
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:28,710
Yes, let's toast to Mr. Li!

60
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:29,750
To Mr. Li!

61
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:30,870
Mr. Li! Mr. Li!

62
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:31,710
Here's to you, Mr. Li!

63
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:32,430
Thank you, Mr. Li.

64
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,470
Thank you for your work.

65
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:46,240
Ms. Fang...

66
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:55,840
Here.

67
00:03:59,360 --> 00:03:59,800
You came.

68
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:00,710
Here.

69
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:01,310
Sit down.

70
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,520
Got you a new set of tableware.

71
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:05,470
Wanzhi?

72
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:07,870
Xingke?

73
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:10,710
Mr. Gao!

74
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:13,430
Aren't you going to introduce us?

75
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,680
Just take a guess yourselves.

76
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,360
She must be your girlfriend, then.

77
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,510
Come on, guys!

78
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,630
Let's all raise a toast to her!

79
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,120
Hear, hear!

80
00:04:23,510 --> 00:04:24,000
Cheers!

81
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,240
They're drunk. Ignore them.

82
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,160
Sit down.

83
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:28,270
Everyone,

84
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:29,560
I didn't know

85
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,720
so many people were here.

86
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,190
I can't drink now.

87
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:33,360
I have a meeting soon.

88
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,560
You all go ahead.

89
00:04:35,270 --> 00:04:36,430
Xingke, keep in touch.

90
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:40,240
What's wrong?

91
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:42,750
Keep it up.

92
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:46,270
Ms. Fang, let's go.

93
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:47,750
I'll take a walk.

94
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,070
Fang Wanzhi?

95
00:05:07,430 --> 00:05:08,040
Fang Wanzhi?

96
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:11,560
Fang Wanzhi!

97
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:13,750
Hey, why are you leaving so soon?

98
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:15,950
You could have skipped the introduction.

99
00:05:16,510 --> 00:05:17,510
Why tell them to guess?

100
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:19,950
I'm sorry.

101
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,190
I'm a bit drunk too.

102
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:22,680
You were misleading others.

103
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,870
You saw right through me.

104
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,560
I'm truly sorry.

105
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:28,800
Why did you sell the company?

106
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,160
You saw the news

107
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,070
and came to congratulate me?

108
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,000
My mistake.

109
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:33,800
I didn't tell you

110
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,360
about them.

111
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:35,720
Just answer my question.

112
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:37,800
I...

113
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,750
Didn't I discuss it with you before?

114
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:42,120
When did you ever discuss it with me?

115
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:43,560
When we went hiking during

116
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:44,950
the last Dragon Boat Festival.

117
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:49,680
I've also been

118
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:50,800
reflecting on this for years.

119
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:51,870
I think

120
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:53,070
I'm not good at management.

121
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:54,560
To be honest,

122
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,360
I still miss it when I first graduated

123
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,950
and became a full-time teacher.

124
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,630
Finding the right job

125
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,310
and achieving self-worth

126
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,600
is both a blessing

127
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:06,000
and a joy.

128
00:06:08,270 --> 00:06:08,870
You also agreed

129
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:10,070
I should be a teacher again, right?

130
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:15,270
You call that discussing it with me?

131
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,600
What else?

132
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,000
You didn't have to discuss it with me.

133
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,680
But I want to know that,

134
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,600
as the founder,

135
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,310
why did you give up so randomly?

136
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,270
Isn't SkyMind

137
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:25,390
your life's work?

138
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,310
I haven't heard of any
management issues.

139
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,920
You didn't have any debts, right?

140
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,190
Of course not.

141
00:06:30,630 --> 00:06:31,680
But I was worried

142
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:32,750
this day would come.

143
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,830
I couldn't run it well,

144
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,120
so I gave up.

145
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:36,870
You coward.

146
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,240
I'm not a hero, anyway.

147
00:06:44,830 --> 00:06:45,870
I heard Li Juan say

148
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,430
you wanted to make

149
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:48,560
Meow Meow Toys the biggest

150
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,630
toy brand in China.

151
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:52,360
And that you won't give up
until you reach the goal,

152
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:52,950
right?

153
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,120
You're the hero.

154
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:55,870
Maybe I should work for you.

155
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:56,950
I could help you

156
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,240
reach that goal.

157
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,360
Why was Xingke there?

158
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:04,070
He's the one

159
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:04,950
who bought my company.

160
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,120
Mr. Li Xingke currently serves

161
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,190
as the chairman of Skymind.

162
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,070
Which report did you see?

163
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,000
Was it just about me?

164
00:07:11,630 --> 00:07:12,630
The one with the most views

165
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:13,680
is a photo of the two of us.

166
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,600
That article was written
pretty objectively.

167
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,270
He's here.

168
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:19,630
Wanzhi.

169
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:22,870
How much debt does he have?

170
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,560
Debt?

171
00:07:24,830 --> 00:07:26,430
How much debt does Skymind have?

172
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:27,720
None.

173
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:28,830
It's been run quite well.

174
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,630
Profits have grown substantially.

175
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:31,750
Else, the acquisition

176
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,750
wouldn't be approved.

177
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,190
How much did he receive?

178
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,000
Wanzhi...

179
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:35,680
That is....

180
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,720
Trade secret, right?

181
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:38,950
I understand.

182
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,120
Does this merger have

183
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,040
anything to do with me?

184
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:43,830
What I'm saying is,

185
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:44,920
did he take advantage

186
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:45,950
of our relationship

187
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,390
to impress you

188
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:48,160
with his company?

189
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:49,680
Wanzhi, listen.

190
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,510
I'm not the one in charge.

191
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:53,310
Acquiring Skymind

192
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,950
was decided by the company's board.

193
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,360
It's strategically important

194
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,680
for our tech sector layout

195
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,560
in the Pearl River Delta.

196
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,560
And, to be honest,

197
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:01,630
I worked hard to get Gao Xiang

198
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,560
to agree to the merger.

199
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,950
I must thank you, Wanzhi.

200
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,190
If it weren't for you,

201
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,480
Mr. Gao wouldn't have

202
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,120
trusted me.

203
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:12,240
I'm sorry

204
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,560
for ruining your party.

205
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:14,920
Wish you a happy cooperation.

206
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:20,310
Gao Xiang,

207
00:08:20,950 --> 00:08:22,240
you're a phony entrepreneur.

208
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,630
I believe unwavering tenacity

209
00:08:23,630 --> 00:08:24,360
is the very soul

210
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,360
of true entrepreneurship.

211
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,950
I look down on those founders

212
00:08:26,950 --> 00:08:27,600
who cash out

213
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:29,000
and walk away like this.

214
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:39,870
You see?

215
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:41,600
I told you.

216
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,240
That is truly

217
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,270
a respectable entrepreneur.

218
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,750
Success or failure aside,

219
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,270
what matters is

220
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:49,670
that an entrepreneur

221
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:51,120
has the soul of one.

222
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:54,960
I'm nothing compared

223
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:57,390
to Fang Wanzhi.

224
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,670
Stop washing the fruit.

225
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:05,840
Come over and have a drink.

226
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,390
Stop forcing Wanzhi to drink.

227
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:09,270
She's been working hard lately.

228
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,270
She'll get drunk easily.

229
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:13,960
Alright.

230
00:09:17,270 --> 00:09:19,200
Am I being too nosy?

231
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:20,600
You're not.

232
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,750
Gao Xiang surely won't be mad at you.

233
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:24,670
But I am!

234
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,840
I've talked quite harshly today.

235
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:32,600
He's just an ordinary friend.

236
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,790
I've really talked too much.

237
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,600
It had nothing to do with me.

238
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:38,440
You still care.

239
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:40,080
If you really saw him

240
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:40,840
as just a friend,

241
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,960
you wouldn't be so upset.

242
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,510
Be honest with yourself.

243
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:44,720
If you ask me,

244
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,670
Gao Xiang is the most capable one.

245
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:47,790
How much did he cash out?

246
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,120
Hurry, tell me.

247
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,630
I'll plan how to manage his assets.

248
00:09:50,670 --> 00:09:52,870
Oh, right. Like you're good at it.

249
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:54,080
With your stocks in such bad shape,

250
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,080
you're still giving advice?

251
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,510
Why do you have

252
00:09:56,510 --> 00:09:57,480
to bring that up?

253
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,630
It's just market conditions.

254
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:00,270
I don't think it can fall any further.

255
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,960
Have a drink with me.

256
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:02,600
Fine.

257
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,120
Here.

258
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,240
I'll head back first.

259
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,670
Hey, don't leave.

260
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,120
The three of us finally

261
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,360
got together,

262
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:11,000
and now you want to head back?

263
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,630
Then we'll all be alone again.

264
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,390
Qian's right.

265
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:16,270
Though my siblings are

266
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:17,390
all in Shenzhen now,

267
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:18,390
everyone is too busy

268
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:19,790
to hang out together.

269
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,750
Luckily, the three of us live nearby.

270
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:23,080
Stay here.

271
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:24,000
Drink some more.

272
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:26,630
You two go ahead.

273
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:28,840
There are over 100 design
drawings for me to review.

274
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,480
Another issue is

275
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,440
that the northern market

276
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,870
has never been fully developed.

277
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,080
From Harbin in the north

278
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,600
to Urumqi in the west,

279
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,270
every provincial capital city

280
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,510
needs a dedicated manager.

281
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:40,360
Juan,

282
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:41,360
give it a thought.

283
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,480
We'll discuss the details

284
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,390
at tomorrow's meeting.

285
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:43,910
Okay.

286
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:44,480
Leaving.

287
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:46,670
Go.

288
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,080
Don't stay too late.

289
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,960
Why is she working so hard?

290
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,030
Health is the most important thing

291
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,550
at our age.

292
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,320
In this state,

293
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,600
could something go wrong with her?

294
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,550
Nothing will go wrong.

295
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:09,150
It's just that as she was ready

296
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:10,360
to build her career,

297
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:12,320
